Binder

Using Binder, you can bind icons, colors,
applications, open methods, and print methods
to files.

Because DeskSet applications come with a
default set of bindings, it is not necessary to
use Binder. You may, however, want to use Binder
to customize your DeskSet Environment, modifying
entries in your personal user data base.

:SaveButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Save

Click SELECT on Save to save your changes to the 
Binder data base.

:UndoButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Undo

Click SELECT on Undo to undo the last operation.

Undo-able operations are those made with the New, 
Duplicate, and Delete buttons.

#####################50###########################
:ViewButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
View

Use the View button to determine which entries you
want to display.

All Entries		Displays all private, 
			system, and network 
			entries.

Shared Entries		Displays all system and 
			network entries.

Personal Entries	Displays only your 
			private user entries.

#####################50###########################

:PropsButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Props

Displays an entry's icon or file type properties.

Icon		Shows the information used to
		display and operate on files.

File Types	Shows the set of files bound to 
		the icons, colors, and 
		applications defined in the Icon
		properties window.

