:PropsDeleteButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Delete

Click SELECT on Delete to remove the File Type
from the current Binder entry.

:Identify:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Identify:

Determines how the current class of files is
recognized.

A class of files is recognized by name or
by content:

by Name		Files are recognized by the 
		pattern in the Pattern field.

by Content	Files are recognized by matching
		file contents instead of the name.

#####################50###########################
:TagOffset:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Tag Offset:

Determines the starting position in the file
where the contents are to be matched.

The default value is 0, the first character of
the file.

:TagType:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Tag Type:

Determines the type of value to be matched in
the file contents: Byte, Short, Long, or String.

#####################50###########################
:TagValue:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Tag Value:

Determines what to look for in the file contents.
This value must be of the type defined in the Data
Type setting.

:TagMask:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/binder.handbook
Tag Mask:

An optional field you can use to define a mask
value for Byte, Short, or Long data types.
